},{"Index":9,"Level":0,"Parameters":{},"ActionType":"Condition-Else","ChildActions":[{"Index":10,"Level":0,"Parameters":{"Type":"Detail-NoQuery","GroupStatement":"","GroupIndex":"","Value":"<b>Example AJAX Country/Region Selection</b><br>\n<i>The Regions are requested from the server whenever the country is selected by firing the <b>ows.Fetch</b> function. The parameters passed are the ModuleID, the current page number (-1), the querystring parameters\n(in this case the key \"action\" identifies that we are requesting \"regions\") and the DOM object id where our result will go. The OWS configuration will return the entire selection box for the regions whenever\nthe ajax request is made and deliver that result into the target DOM object below - named: \"spnRegions\"</i>\n<br/>\n<u>Country</u>\n<br/>\n<select name=\"frmCountry\" onchange=\"ows.Fetch('[ModuleID,System]',-1,'action=regions','spnRegions');\">\n<option>Select a Country</option>\n{SUBQUERY,\n\tName=\"GetCountries\",\n\tQuery=\"Select Text,EntryID from Lists where ListName='Country'\",\n\tFormat=\"<option value='\\[EntryID\\]'>\\[Text\\]</option>\",\n\tUseCache=\"True\"\n}\n</select>\n<br/>\n\n<u>Region</u>\n<br/>\n<span id=\"spnRegions\">\nSelect a Country First\n<!--Add a Region Element that has an empty value so frmRegion contains something on a postback of a surrounding form-->\n<input name=\"frmRegion\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"\"/>\n</span>","Connection":"","Filter":"","CacheTime":"","CacheName":"","CacheShared":"false"},"ActionType":"Template","ChildActions":[]}]}],"query":"","filter":"","customConnection":"","listItem":"","listAItem":"","defaultItem":"","noqueryItem":"","SearchQuery":"","SearchTitle":"","SearchLink":"","SearchAuthor":"","SearchDate":"","SearchKey":"","SearchContent":"","SearchDescription":"","Version":"20","Index":"Country.Region.AJAX.Dropdown","enableAJAXPaging":"false","enableAJAXPageHistory":"false","customAJAXPageHistory":"","disableOpenScript":false,"enableSilverlight":false,"ja